title: Pepsi, Al-Zamil and Pinehill win in SAGCO Cup
text:
Electro squad
KMA Perera
JEDDAH — Pepsi secured a hard fought 83-78 victory against Electro in the second week action of the first round of SAGCO Basketball Cup 2015 here over the weekend.
Although Electro led the second and third quarters, James Casas of Pepsi rose to the occasion with accurate shooting to score 30 points with several assists from Nino Luyahan, who made 18.
Delta Team rallied to secure a nail-biting one-point win, 63-62, against Al-Tayar. Delta’s Ostanal and Ballinan made valiant play to penetrate Al-Tayar defense to basket crucial points in the fourth quarter, and that turned the game Delta’s way.
The Game between Al-Zamil and Techno Glass was also a close affair. Darwin Genil scored 30 points to ensure 67-60 victory for Al-Zamil.
Pinehill won 82-72 over Attieh Steel. D. Edu and D. Lugue made combined efforts with several rebounds and assists to ensure their team led all four quarters.
Al-Yanabie gained an easy 82-70 victory over debutant Mahmood Saeed. Printopack’s, Ronald Domantay’s highest score of 33 for the weekend couldn’t stop Attieh Steel beat them 67-59.
SCORES
Pepsi 83 — James Casas 30, Nino Luyahan 1 . Electro 78 — W. Berrer 19 R. Caguicia 17.
Delta 63 — Ostanal 20, Ballinan 12 and Al-Tayar 62 — A. Sandoval 21, L. Lumbao 16.
Al-Zamil 67 — Darwin Genil 30, Patrick Pomoy 13. Techno Glass 60, Jeff Angeles 19, Junrey Reyes 19.
Pinehill 82 — D. Lugue 19, M. Membrillos 17. Al-Attieh Steel 72 — R. Goniabo 16, E. Sanchez 14.
Al-Yanabie 82 — J. Monding 14, M. Diloy 12. Mahmood Saeed 70 — L. Deldo 16.
Atteih Steel 67 — M. Nidoy 17, D. Arellano 17 and Printopack 59 — Ronald Domantay 33, Michael Domantay 8.
